        "\n",
        "# Module Learning Objectives {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
        "Module 0 builds the computational and mathematical foundation for the rest of AD698. By the end of this module, students should be able to:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. work reliably in Google Colab and Google Drive\n",
        "2. inspect and manipulate tensors in PyTorch\n",
        "3. connect mathematical objects such as vectors, matrices, and tensors to code\n",
        "4. prepare for later neural-network, NLP, and generative AI workflows\n",
        "\n",
        "## Tutorial Learning Objectives {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
        "By the end of this tutorial, you should be able to:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Start and validate a GPU runtime.\n",
        "2. Mount and organize Google Drive for AD698.\n",
        "3. Build and manipulate tensors of different ranks.\n",
        "4. Run a simple CPU vs GPU comparison.\n",
        "\n",
        "## How This Tutorial Connects {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
